  <section condition="TITLE=Administration: Trust Relationship;PERM=sy_bank_trust_relationship_access;ACCESS=SY_TRS_B"
           id="TRL" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As a bank group administrator, you can link customers
    across different banks or branches by creating a trust relationship. You
    can then link users of these customers and enable them to view account
    balances in a uni-directional or bi-directional exchange of
    information.</para>

    <note>
      <para role="TEXT">Trust relationship is not available for multi-bank
      customers.</para>
    </note>
</section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
      xpointer="ent_trust_relationship"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold"><xi:include
      href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_trust_relationship"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /></emphasis> function, from
      the toolbar, select <emphasis>System Features</emphasis> from the home
      page, then select <emphasis><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
      xpointer="ent_trust_relationship"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /></emphasis> from the left
      navigation menu.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
      xpointer="ent_trust_relationship"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> - Customer Level
      List</title>

      <para role="TEXT">You (Bank Group Administrators) can use this option to
      create and manage trust relationship details for your Bank's customers.
      When you select the <guisubmenu>Customer Level</guisubmenu> option, you
      are presented with a list of all the existing customer level trust
      relationships for your banks. You can search the list by entering search
      criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">From Bank</guilabel>,
      <guilabel>To Bank</guilabel>, <guilabel>From Customer</guilabel>,
      <guilabel>To Customer</guilabel>, <guilabel>Relation</guilabel> (*,
      Uni-directional and Bi-directional), <guilabel>Relationship
      Status</guilabel> (*, Active and Inactive), <guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel> fields
      at the top of the page. Click the <guilabel>Download File</guilabel>
      button to download the list in CSV and Spreadsheet (MS Excel)
      format.</para>

      <note>
        <para><guilabel>Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel>
        fields are available only if maker-checker functionality is
        enabled.</para>
      </note>

      <para role="TEXT">You can view the following columns in the list of
      trust relationships:</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">From
              Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the bank to which
              the customer establishing the trust relationship belongs to.
              </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">To
              Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the bank to which
              the customer with whom the relationship is established with
              belongs to.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">From
              Customer</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the customer from
              where Regional Account View may be accessed.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">To
              Customer</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the customer with
              whom the trust relationship is established.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Relation</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Type of relationship established at
              the customer level, whether Uni-directional or Bi-directional.
              </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Relationship Status</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Status of the relationship, whether
              active or inactive. </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry
              valign="top"><para><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Indicates the status of the pending
              record set by the checker.</para><note>
                  <para>This column is available if maker-checker
                  functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para><guilabel>Maker User
              </guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Displays the user ID of the maker of
              the transaction.</para><note>
                  <para>This column is available if maker-checker
                  functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <para role="TEXT">You can modify a trust relationship by clicking the
      <guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                       width="4mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column, view it in
      non-editable mode by clicking the <guibutton>View</guibutton>
      <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_popup.gif" role="ICON_POPUP"
                       width="4.5mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon, or delete it by clicking the <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                       width="4mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon.</para>

      <note>
        <para role="TEXT">Once user-level associations are set up, you cannot
        delete a trust relationship.</para>
      </note>

      <para role="TEXT">Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add a new trust
      relationship</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to add a trust
      relationship. <guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> and <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Add a new trust relationship </guibutton>display the
      same form, but in the case of <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Edit</guibutton>, the <guilabel>From Bank</guilabel>,
      <guilabel>To Bank</guilabel>, <guilabel>From Customer</guilabel> and
      <guilabel>To Customer</guilabel> fields are not editable.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Cancel a transaction by clicking on the
      <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_cancel.gif" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon or approve by clicking the
      <guibutton>Action</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_action.gif" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon. These icons are available if maker-checker
      is enabled for your profile.</para>

