    <section role="ITEM">
      <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
      xpointer="ent_trust_relationship"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> - User Level List</title>

      <para role="TEXT">You (Bank Group Administrators) can use this option to
      create and manage trust relationship details for users of customers in
      your Banks. When you select this option, you are presented with a list
      of all the existing customer level trust relationships for your bank's
      customers. You can search the list by entering search criteria in the
      <guilabel moreinfo="none">From Bank</guilabel>, <guilabel>To
      Bank</guilabel>, <guilabel>From Customer</guilabel>, <guilabel>To
      Customer</guilabel>, <guilabel>Relation</guilabel> (*, Uni-directional
      and Bi-directional) and <guilabel>Relationship Status</guilabel> (*,
      Active and Inactive) fields at the top of the page. Click the
      <guilabel>Download File</guilabel> button to download the list in CSV
      and Spreadsheet (MS Excel) format.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">You can view the following columns in the list of user
      level trust relationships:</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">From
              Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the bank to which
              the customer establishing the trust relationship belongs to.
              </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">To
              Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the bank to which
              the customer with whom the relationship is established with
              belongs to.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">From
              Customer</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the customer
              creating the trust relationship.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">To
              Customer</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name of the customer with
              whom the trust relationship is created.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
